research question

How about the historical registration situation of Chinese Internet companies?

Description Protocol Data

Description

The overall layout was a matrix map by the time dimension, which could be called ‘small multiples.’ The color of each area represented the registration counting, the more red, the more company counting. The position of each area was determined by the latitude and longitude of the relative province on the map.

What needed to be informed here for the visualization was that the dataset was of some inaccuracy, since the data source was shared on open-source platform Github despite an official organization. Thus, the purpose of this visualization was to emphasize the form and method of visualization design. Overall, through a macro perspective, the Chinese Internet industry developed rapidly during the 40 years from 1980 to 2019. Every year, many new Internet companies registered in various provinces across all over the country since 2004, and the registration counting showed a trend of increasing over time.

Protocol

From Github open source, the entire database for 34 provinces in China from 1978 to 2019 was collected. After selecting useful fields of the data, the final Internet company CSV file was obtained,including more than 140,000 data. Importing the Internet company registration data file into Tableau to calculate how many companies were registered on each year of each province, the visualization was embodied by mapping the counts by color and positioning of provinces on the map. Through Adobe Illustrator, the final visualization was demonstrated by manually shaped as small multiples.
